# 7.8 Best Practice

## Core Principles

- Build spacing early
- Use speed control before vectoring
- Maintain stable approaches
- Avoid last-minute corrections

---

## Golden Rules

- Do not chase spacing late
- Do not over-control aircraft
- Keep the sequence predictable

---

## Professional Standard

A well-managed sequence will demonstrate:

- Consistent spacing on final
- Minimal controller intervention
- Smooth and continuous traffic flow

---

## Key Takeaway

> The best controllers solve problems before they exist.
